Carrier plate Chapter 2.2

2.2.1 Adjusting the carrier plate

Prior to performing any work on electrical components, unplug the instrument from mains.

1. Put on carrier plate (1) and tighten clamping screw (2).

2. Put on carousel cover (3) and rotate clockwise until pin (4) snaps into place, then rotate careful- ly approx. 3/4 turn to fasten.

If too much torque is applied, the thread may become stripped.

3. Move elevation mechanism upwards - see chap- ter 10.1 of the operating instructions.

4. Place hook (5) for tissue basket (6) in position 1 - see chapter 10.1 of the operating instructions.

5. Put glass beakers (7) in position 1 and 2 and hang tissue basket (6) on hook (5).

6. Carefully move the elevation mechanism down- wards - see chapter 10.1 of the operating instruc- tions - when lowering the mechanism, the tissue basket (6) must be immersed centrically into the glass beaker (7). If the tissue basket is not properly centered, move the elevation mechanism upwards, open screws (8) and adjust carrier plate (1) so that tis- sue basket (6) enters glass beaker (7) centrically.

7. Tighten screws (8).

