7.1 Adjustments

7.1.1 Code disk modification; new adjustment tool (TP 1020 from SN 2391/032005 onwards)

In response to reported errors or error messages such as • E:03, • incorrect station indication • mechanical obstructions • program abortion without error message

a modification of the code disk had to be made. In conjunction with this, chapter 2 of the Service Manual 2.0 / 2007 has to be amended with the present information. Please update your documents accordingly.

This change is expected to considerably reduce the above mentioned faults on the one hand, and should help to simplify and better structure any later adjustment in the field. It is no longer necessary to elaborately adjust the code disk via setscrews. A further add-on allowing to open the tower without dismantling the carousel is in preparation.

Adjustment tool #042240818 has been added to the adjustment tools to complement and simplify the adjustments described in chapter 2 (Service Manual 2.0 / 2007). It is used for precise station positioning of the code disk and adjustment of the elevation and rotation mechanism as described below. As the suspension of the code disk has been modified, points 4) and 5) can only be performed on TP1020 from SN 2391/032005 onwards.

Note: A refurbishment from old to new code disk cannot be performed in the field and will begiven NO TECHNICAL SUPPORT!

The holder is no longer fixed to the center tube with two setscrews but rather by clamping.

The code disk has three oblong holes now to allow for rotating while fixing it to the holder. Another two adjustment holes have been added for alignment with horizontal Pos PCB using adjusting tool # 042240818.

All previous TP1020 adjustment tools are still valid and used.

Following is an overview of the TP1020 adjustment tools (2 pages) and an amendment of the elevation / rotation mechanism adjustment description (5 pages).

