7.2 Software

7.2.1 Service Software Version 1.10 and higher Starting with version 1.10, the TP1020 instrument software has been enhanced with additional features to support instrument functions and service diagnosis.

Configuration: Signal Level? 4 1-4 Volume of  alarm signal 3rd Wax Bath? No Yes/ No 3 rd  wax bath for two-basket double loading Prog Reset? No Yes/ No Default user programs System Reset? No Yes/ No Reset time, rotation cycles Service Mode? No Yes/ No Diagnostic mode Work.Hours Indication only Cycles Indication only

Start and Exit Service Mode: • Activate Configuration Mode • Activate Service Mode • Exit Service Mode • Service Programs PA und PB • Counter for working hours • Counter for rotation cycles

Activate Configuration Mode If possible, travel TP1020 to station U01 and switch off for about 60 seconds. Configuration Mode is activated by pressing the  PROG key  while or after switching the instrument on with the  mains switch . The instruments immediately comes up with the  Configuration Mode .

Activate des Service Mode Use arrow right / left keys to jump to submenu (e.g. Service Mode). The prompt  ServiceMode?  is confirmed with keys  + (YES)  and  Prog . After completing the initialization phase, the software starts the  Service Mode and the two service programs PA and PB are available to test instrument functions.

Service programs PA and PB Both programs can be selected like in normal operating mode. If the instrument is not at station U01 when starting program B, then program A is executed until station U01 is reached.

Exit Service Mode The Service Mode is automatically terminated by switching the instrument off with the  mains switch  or also by a  mains voltage failure . When powered up the next time, the instrument will be in normal  Operating Mode .

