7.2.2 Service programm and counters

Service programs PA and PB • Program PA: The rotor continuously turns from one station to the next  without lowering into the stations . Program PA cannot be changed. • Program PB: Process sequence like in a normal program  with lowering into the stations ,  on condition that the stations have a set infiltration time of > 0. Vacuum and infiltration time are set as usual, but the start time function cannot be programmed.

Characteristics: • Infiltration When activating the service mode, the infiltration time is defaulted to 1 min at all stations, and, if the in- strument has this option, vacuum is activated at all stations. At a infiltration time of 1 min., at stations without active vacuum the actual infiltration time is reduced to 15 seconds to speed up the process.

• Drain phase In Service Mode the drain phase is disabled, i.e. the rotor does not pause for 1 min prior to turning to the next station. Disabling the drain pause increases the number of rotary cycles in a certain period and con- siderably shortens the fill and diagnostic phase.

• Wax bath control In Service Mode no  wax bath control W:01 – W:06  is performed in order to avoid that the process is aborted by a wax bath alarm during a continous test run. Other malfunctions which may abort the pro- cess in normal Operating Mode such as  jams or blockings (e.g. E0:03)  will also cause termination in Service Mode.

Work.hours - Counter of operating times A counter of operating times is implemented for preventative maintenance work, in particular for instru- ments using chloroform and it records instrument on-time in minutes. The counter can be selected in Ser- vice mode as parameter  Work.hours . The complete operating hours up to max. 99999h are indicated and are automatically set to 0h in case of overflow. In the  Work.hours menu  the working hours counter can be deliberately reset to 0 hours by pressing the PROG and STOP  keys simultanously. The counter value is not modified when doing a  SystemReset .

Cycles - Counter of Rotary Cycles A counter of rotary cycles is installed to allow evaluating the mechanical drive components. It counts the complete rotations of the rotor. The counter value is increased by one increment when going from station 12 to 01. It can be selected in Service mode as parameter  Cycles . The maximum value is 99999 rotations and is reset to 0 after overflow. In the  Cycles menu  the rotary cycles counter can be deliberately reset to 0 cycles by pressing the  PROG and STOP  keys simultanously. The rotary cycles counter‘s value is reset to 0 cycles when doing a  System- Reset .

